  "body": "### Overview\r\n\r\nI am wanting to install [kollateral](https://github.com/kollateral/kollateral) as a dependency, but it has a different project structure than brownie expects.\r\n\r\nThe repo also does not have any git tags.\r\n\r\n### Specification\r\n\r\n`.../main.py` has `if not install_path.joinpath(\"contracts\").exists():`. For now I've just commented this out, since contracts is just deeper in the project, but I think having this be a configurable value would work well.\r\n\r\nFor the lack of tags, it would be nice if we could just specify a full git hash.\r\n",
